'Communism' was fine if you don't have a problem with being dragged out of bed at night and shipped off to some gulag somewhere or hunted down like a dog because you dared to criticise the state in even minor ways.  If you want a good feel for what Soviet style communism was like read &quot;The Gulag Archipelago&quot; by Aleksandr Isaevich Solzhenitsyn or &quot;Korolev: How One Man Masterminded the Soviet Drive to Beat America to the Moon&quot; by James Harford.  Democracy and human rights might make progress inefficient but I'd much rather put up with inefficiency than to live in constant fear of being dragged off never to be seen again for what we would consider minor offenses or not offenses at all. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=hamster@nuclearspace>Hamster</A> at: 1/7/03 1:32:31 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=projectorion>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Nuclear Renaissance Man</span><br>  Posts: 2833<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/7/03 11:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=673.topic&index=33>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://news.nationalgeographic.com/news/2001/05/images/021011_nuclear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.nuclearspace.com/ezboard/images/posticons/zilla.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: China and Space.</span><hr size=1> Case in point. I thought my post was pretty clear. I do not condone the Russian communist regime. I was blathering about the actual system itself. Communism. If you read its fundamental description it compares very favourably against republics. Democracy is also very nice on paper. However, both are corruptible. Leaders will abuse the system in